ash$nCrucially, this finding is at the assemblage level. Consequently, the$\backslash$nrelative abundances and identities of ant species that are present in an$\backslash$nassemblage can change in accordance with environmental conditions over$\backslash$nelevation, latitude and relatively short time spans. These findings$\backslash$nsuggest that there are important constraints on how ectotherm$\backslash$nassemblages may be able to respond to rapidly changing environmental$\backslash$nconditions.},
